Package: brfssTools
Title: Harmonize Longitudinal BRFSS Survey Data
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Nathan", "Parsons", , "nathan.f.parsons@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for harmonizing the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance
    System (BRFSS) survey data across years. The crosswalk is anchored on
    the user's most recent year of data: a 'draft' function reads the
    variable list from the latest year's data file and produces a
    starting crosswalk where each variable becomes a 'concept_id', the
    user fills in equivalents for older years via a Shiny editor, and
    individual cells can be flagged 'calculated' to store inline YAML
    that defines a year-specific computation. Domain assignment is
    pre-filled where possible from the shipped CDC codebook reference
    and left as 'Unassigned' otherwise for user review.
